events.description: The release of industrial production data for Estonia for the month of December 2025.

facts.fact_text: Industrial production in Estonia rose by 0.2% year-on-year in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: Industrial production in Estonia rose by 0.2% year-on-year in December 2025

facts.fact_text: Manufacturing output growth moderated to 0.4% in December from 4.5% in November.

evidences.evidence_text: Manufacturing output growth moderated (0.4% vs 4.5% in November)

facts.fact_text: Output in mining and quarrying surged to 61.9% from 10.0%.

evidences.evidence_text: output in mining and quarrying surged to 61.9% from 10.0%

facts.fact_text: Industrial production fell by 1.8% on a monthly basis in December.

evidences.evidence_text: On a monthly basis, industrial production fell by 1.8% in December

claims.claim_text: Estonia's industrial output growth eased in December.

evidences.evidence_text: Estonia Industrial Output Growth Eases in December

claims.claim_text: Manufacturing output growth was largely weighed down by declines in specific sectors like textiles and coke.

evidences.evidence_text: Manufacturing output growth moderated... largely weighed by declines in textiles (-8.4% vs 2.5%), wearing apparel (-10.5% vs 13.8%), coke and refined petroleum products (-22.6% vs 11.1%)

evidence.evidence_text: Manufacturing output growth moderated... largely weighed by declines in textiles
Estonia Industrial Output Growth Eases in December
Meanwhile, output in mining and quarrying surged to 61.9% from 10.0%
